cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the modeling of vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs) and the propagation of signals in such networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves the use of mathematical models and simulations, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also deals with system-level simulations, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of measurements and validation, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
